PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F433A1775578269
OL,3,CPine martens' 'elusive woodland
OL,4,Cantics' captured on camera
OL,6,FPine martens had been missing from the
OL,7,Fregion for more than 100 years after
OL,8,Fhaving been hunted and trapped to
OL,9,Fextinction.
OL,11,FThe animals are the size of a small
OL,12,Fcat and like to climb trees in search
OL,13,Fof food which includes wild fruits,
OL,14,Fmice, grey squirrels, and other small
OL,15,Fprey.
OL,17,FIn autumn 2024, 15 pine martens were
OL,18,Freleased at secret woodland locations
OL,19,Fon Dartmoor; while in autumn 2025 a
OL,20,Ffurther 19 animals were released at
OL,21,Fundisclosed spots on Exmoor.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/10
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,434,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F433A1775578269
OL,3,CPine martens' 'elusive woodland
OL,4,Cantics' captured on camera
OL,6,FThe reintroductions were the work of
OL,7,Fthe Two Moors Pine Marten Project
OL,8,Fwhich is supported by The National
OL,9,FLottery Heritage Fund.
OL,11,FThe project is led by the charity
OL,12,FDevon Wildlife Trust and is a
OL,13,Fpartnership between seven
OL,14,Forganisations, including the National
OL,15,FTrust and Forestry England.
OL,17,FTracking collars given to each animal
OL,18,Fbefore release have allowed the
OL,19,Fproject to monitor their progress.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/10
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,434,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F433A1775578269
OL,3,CPine martens' 'elusive woodland
OL,4,Cantics' captured on camera
OL,6,FTracey Hamston, the Two Moors Pine
OL,7,FMarten Project Lead, said: "The
OL,8,Fcollars have meant we can track the
OL,9,Fanimals' movements.
OL,11,F"The results show that some pine
OL,12,Fmartens stayed close to where they
OL,13,Fwere released, but others travelled
OL,14,Fsome distance, in a few cases more
OL,15,Fthan 20 miles.
OL,17,F"The Dartmoor pine martens seem now to
OL,18,Fhave settled forming their own
OL,19,Findividual territories.
OL,26,@oD@\OU
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/10
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,434,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F433A1775578269
OL,3,CPine martens' 'elusive woodland
OL,4,Cantics' captured on camera
OL,6,F"Some of the Exmoor animals still seem
OL,7,Fto be mobile but we'd expect most to
OL,8,Fsettle and establish a territory soon.
OL,10,F"It's been amazing to see where the
OL,11,Fpine martens have travelled since
OL,12,Ftheir release. We can see that they've
OL,13,Fbeen thoroughly exploring the
OL,14,Flandscape before settling into their
OL,15,Fnew woodland homes."
OL,17,FThe pine martens' collars are designed
OL,18,Fto cease to function and drop off
OL,19,Fafter six months.
OL,26,@wD@TO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/10
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,434,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F433A1775578269
OL,3,CPine martens' 'elusive woodland
OL,4,Cantics' captured on camera
OL,6,FIn their place the project is now
OL,7,Fseeking to track the animals' progress
OL,8,Fusing remote cameras positioned in
OL,9,Flocal woodlands.
OL,11,FLast July, one of these cameras
OL,12,Frecorded images of a female pine
OL,13,Fmarten and her three kits (youngsters)
OL,14,Fas they moved through a Dartmoor
OL,15,Fwoodland. This was the first proof
OL,16,Fthat the animals had bred successfully.
OL,18,FTracey said: "This was the news we
OL,19,Fwere waiting for ` proof that the pine
OL,20,Fmartens have established themselves
OL,21,Fand are doing well.
OL,26,@zD@NOU
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/10
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,434,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43307
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F433A1775578269
OL,3,CPine martens' 'elusive woodland
OL,4,Cantics' captured on camera
OL,6,FThis year's kits should be being born
OL,7,Fon both Dartmoor and Exmoor around
OL,8,Fnow. We hope to see evidence of this
OL,9,Fon our cameras when the kits become
OL,10,Fmore active in May and June."
OL,12,FAbby Parravani, forest planner at
OL,13,FForestry England, said: "Forestry
OL,14,FEngland is proud to be a partner in
OL,15,Fthe Two Moors Pine Marten project.
OL,17,F"The encouraging results from collar
OL,18,Ftracking and camera trap monitoring
OL,19,Fare hugely rewarding for all involved
OL,20,Fin the project.
OL,26,@rD@]O]uD@YOU
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/10
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,434,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43308
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F433A1775578269
OL,3,CPine martens' 'elusive woodland
OL,4,Cantics' captured on camera
OL,6,F"As omnivores and predators, pine
OL,7,Fmartens fulfil an important role in
OL,8,Fwoodland ecosystems, helping to
OL,9,Fincrease the resilience of forests, so
OL,10,Fwe are thrilled that this native
OL,11,Fspecies is once again establishing in
OL,12,Fwoodlands in the South West."
OL,14,FThe Two Moors Pine Marten Project is
OL,15,Fnow appealing to the public to help it
OL,16,Fkeep tabs on the pine martens'
OL,17,Fwhereabouts.
OL,19,FIt is asking anyone who sees a pine
OL,20,Fmarten in the region to let them know
OL,21,Fwhere and when they spot them.
OL,26,@tD@]O]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/10
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,434,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43309
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F433A1775578269
OL,3,CPine martens' 'elusive woodland
OL,4,Cantics' captured on camera
OL,6,FThe project would especially welcome
OL,7,Fphotos or video of sightings. All
OL,8,Frecords of pine marten encounters can
OL,9,Fbe sent to a dedicated email address:
OL,10,Fpinemartens@ devonwildlifetrust.org
OL,12,FThe precise locations of the animals
OL,13,Fare being kept secret by the project
OL,14,Fto minimise disturbance.
OL,16,FThe project is also keen to hear from
OL,17,Fwoodland owners with wildlife cameras,
OL,18,Fespecially those on or close to
OL,19,FDartmoor and Exmoor, who would be
OL,20,Fhappy to take part in its Woodland
OL,21,FSurvey.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G9/10
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
